de.larssh.utils.text

Class Csv

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.larssh.utils.collection.ProxiedCollection<E>
      • de.larssh.utils.collection.ProxiedList<CsvRow>
        • de.larssh.utils.text.Csv
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<CsvRow>, Collection<CsvRow>, List<CsvRow>

    public class Csv
extends ProxiedList<CsvRow>
    This class represents CSV data, consisting of rows of values, implementing List<String> for convenience reasons.

    The first row is referenced as header row and CsvRow instances allow to retrieve their values by the column's CSV header value.

    Instances of this class can be marked unmodifiable using unmodifiable(). Afterwards applying modifying actions on that instance results in an UnsupportedOperationException.

      • addAllList

        public boolean addAllList(Collection<? extends List<String>> collection)
        Adds all of the CSV rows in collection to this CSV object.

        The behavior of this operation is undefined if the specified collection is modified while the operation is in progress. (This implies, that the behavior of this call is undefined if the specified collection is this CSV object, and this CSV object is non-empty.)

        Parameters:
        collection - the collection containing CSV rows to be added
        Returns:
        true if this CSV object changed as a result of the call, else false
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - if this CSV object is unmodifiable
